"script": "If you pulled every blood vessel out of your body and laid them end to end, they'd stretch about 60,000 miles. That's enough to wrap around the entire planet more than twice. Most of that length is microscopic capillaries, each one thinner than a single human hair. You see, these tiny tubes thread into every inch of you, feeding each cell its oxygen. And your heart pushes blood through this whole network in under a minute. So hidden inside your body is a road longer than the trip to the Moon, packed into a space smaller than a suitcase.",
